5 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 7-414, is
6 amended to read as follows:
7 Section 7-414. A. The provisions of the Oklahoma Milk and Milk
8 Products Act shall not be construed to:
9 1. Include incidental sales of raw milk directly to consumers
10 at the farm where the milk is produced or directly to consumers
11 pursuant to provisions provided by the Homemade Food Freedom Act;
12 2. Preclude the advertising of the incidental sale of goat
13 milk; and
14 3. Prohibit any farmer or producer from making cheese using
15 milk or cream produced on the farm of such farmer or producer.
16 B. For purposes of this section, incidental sales of goat milk
17 are those sales where the average monthly number of gallons sold
18 does not exceed one hundred (100).
19 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
